==Game records== ===Biggest wins=== *The largest difference in qualifying rounds is +43: **[[Riesen Ludwigsburg]] beat [[KK Bosna Royal|Bosna]] 59–102 (+43) in [[2017–18 Basketball Champions League|2017–18]] **[[BC Nizhny Novgorod|Nizhny Novgorod]] beat [[FC Porto (basketball)|Porto]] 92–49 (+43) in [[2018–19 Basketball Champions League|2018–19]] **[[Kataja BC|Kataja]] beat [[Södertälje Kings]] 97–58 (+39) in [[2016–17 Basketball Champions League|2016–17]] **[[Aris B.C.|Aris]] beat [[BC Dinamo Tbilisi|Dinamo Tbilisi]] 92–54 (+38) in [[2018–19 Basketball Champions League|2018–19]]
*The following teams won a single match by 40 points or more in the regular season of the Basketball Champions League: **[[CB 1939 Canarias|Canarias]] beat [[Orlandina Basket|Orlandina]] 59–106 (+47) in [[2017–18 Basketball Champions League|2017–18]] **[[CB 1939 Canarias|Canarias]] beat [[KK Mornar|Mornar]] 103–57 (+46) in [[2016–17 Basketball Champions League|2016–17]] **[[Basketball Nymburk|Nymburk]] beat [[Bakken Bears]] 114–70 (+44) in [[2016–17 Basketball Champions League|2016–17]] **[[AEK B.C.|AEK]] beat [[Szolnoki Olaj KK|Szolnoki Olaj]] 92–59 (+43) in [[2016–17 Basketball Champions League|2016–17]] **[[Riesen Ludwigsburg]] beat [[Szolnoki Olaj KK|Szolnoki Olaj]] 99–56 (+43) in [[2016–17 Basketball Champions League|2016–17]] **[[BC Neptūnas|Neptūnas]] beat [[Gaziantep Basketbol|Gaziantep]] 114–73 (+41) in [[2017–18 Basketball Champions League|2017–18]] **[[CB 1939 Canarias|Canarias]] beat [[Orlandina Basket|Orlandina]] 88–47 (+41) in [[2017–18 Basketball Champions League|2017–18]]
*The following teams won a single match by 20 points or more in the playoffs of the Basketball Champions League: **[[AS Monaco Basket|Monaco]] beat [[Basket Zielona Góra|Zielona Góra]] 90–60 (+30) in [[2017–18 Basketball Champions League|2017–18]] **[[CB 1939 Canarias|Canarias]] beat [[P.A.O.K. B.C.|PAOK]] 80–54 (+26) in [[2016–17 Basketball Champions League|2016–17]] **[[Riesen Ludwigsburg]] beat [[EWE Baskets Oldenburg|Oldenburg]] 63–88 (+25) in [[2017–18 Basketball Champions League|2017–18]] **[[Dinamo Basket Sassari|Dinamo Sassari]] beat [[Basketball Nymburk|Nymburk]] 94–72 (+22) in [[2016–17 Basketball Champions League|2016–17]] **[[AS Monaco Basket|Monaco]] beat [[Riesen Ludwigsburg]] 65–87 (+22) in [[2017–18 Basketball Champions League|2017–18]], the largest difference in a Final Four **[[AEK B.C.|AEK]] beat [[BC Juventus|Juventus]] 75–54 (+21) in [[2016–17 Basketball Champions League|2016–17]] **[[Basketball Nymburk|Nymburk]] beat [[Dinamo Basket Sassari|Dinamo Sassari]] 84–63 (+21) in [[2016–17 Basketball Champions League|2016–17]] **[[Pınar Karşıyaka|Karşıyaka]] beat [[Skyliners Frankfurt]] 72–52 (+20) in [[2016–17 Basketball Champions League|2016–17]]
===Biggest two leg wins=== *[[Nanterre 92]] holds the overall record by beating [[Kauhajoki Karhu|Karhu]] 182–112 (+70) in the qualifying round in [[2018–19 Basketball Champions League|2018–19]]. They beat the Finns by 54–91 and 91–58 *[[Riesen Ludwigsburg]] has the second overall record by beating [[KK Bosna Royal|Bosna]] 187–118 (+69) in the qualifying round in [[2017–18 Basketball Champions League|2017–18]]. They beat the Bosnians by 59–85 and 102–59 *[[Aris B.C.|Aris]] has the third record by beating [[BC Dinamo Tbilisi|Dinamo Tbilisi]] 182–118 (+64) in the qualifying round in [[2018–19 Basketball Champions League|2018–19]]. They beat the Georgians by 64–90 and 92–54 *As for the regular season, record belongs to [[CB 1939 Canarias|Canarias]], who beat [[Orlandina Basket|Orlandina]] 194–106 (+88, 88–47 at home, 59–106 away) in [[2017–18 Basketball Champions League|2017–18]] *[[AS Monaco Basket|Monaco]] holds the biggest margin of overall home and away result in the Basketball Champions League era in playoffs. They beat [[Basket Zielona Góra|Zielona Góra]] 174–142 (+32, 82–84 win away, 90–60, win at home) in the round of 16 in [[2017–18 Basketball Champions League|2017–18]]
===Most overtimes in a match=== *Two matches were decided after playing three overtimes: **[[Rosa Radom|Radom]] beat [[PAOK B.C.|PAOK]] 93–85 (6–6, 8–8, 14–6) in [[2016–17 Basketball Champions League|2016–17]] **[[Reyer Venezia Mestre|Reyer Venezia]] beat [[Banvit B.K.|Banvit]] 108–101 (11–11, 4–4, 13–6) in [[2017–18 Basketball Champions League|2017–18]] *Other three matches, after playing two: **[[S.S. Felice Scandone|Felice Scandone]] beat [[BC Nizhny Novgorod|Nizhny Novgorod]] 93–100 (15–15, 3–10) in [[2018–19 Basketball Champions League|2018–19]] **[[AEK B.C.|AEK Athens]] beat [[Basketball Nymburk|Nymburk]] 93–94 (4–4, 7–8) in [[2018–19 Basketball Champions League|2018–19]] **[[Reyer Venezia Mestre|Reyer Venezia]] beat [[Hapoel Holon B.C.|Hapoel Holon]] 111–104 (12–12, 17–10) in [[2018–19 Basketball Champions League|2018–19]]
===Highest scorings=== *Four teams scored more than 110 points in a game: **[[Telekom Baskets Bonn|Bonn]] scored 114 points against [[BK Opava|Opava]] (114–77) in the regular season in [[2018–19 Basketball Champions League|2018–19]] **[[BC Neptūnas|Neptūnas]] scored 114 points against [[Gaziantep Basketbol|Gaziantep]] (114–73) in the regular season in [[2017–18 Basketball Champions League|2017–18]] **[[BC Avtodor Saratov|Avtodor]] scored 113 points against [[Kataja BC|Kataja]] (113–84) in the regular season in [[2016–17 Basketball Champions League|2016–17]] **[[Reyer Venezia Mestre|Reyer Venezia]] scored 111 points against [[Hapoel Holon]] (111–104) in the regular season in [[2018–19 Basketball Champions League|2018–19]]
===Lowest scorings=== *Three teams scored less than 49 points in a match:
**[[Skyliners Frankfurt]] scored 47 points against [[AS Monaco Basket|Monaco]] (65–47) in the regular season in [[2017–18 Basketball Champions League|2017–18]]. This is the overall record for all Basketball Champions League matches **[[Orlandina Basket|Orlandina]] scored 47 points against [[CB 1939 Canarias|Canarias]] (88–47) in the regular season in [[2017–18 Basketball Champions League|2017–18]] **[[Banvit B.K.|Banvit]] scored 48 points against [[Rosa Radom|Radom]] (49–48) in the regular season in [[2017–18 Basketball Champions League|2017–18]] *[[S.S. Felice Scandone|Felice Scandone]] scored 49 points against [[Reyer Venezia Mestre|Reyer Venezia]] (53–49) in the round of 16 in [[2016–17 Basketball Champions League|2016–17]]. This is the overall record for the Basketball Champions League playoffs
===Most points in a match=== *In six matches, the overall scoring was more than 200 points: **[[Reyer Venezia Mestre|Reyer Venezia]] beat 111–104 (215 points) [[Hapoel Holon B.C.|Hapoel Holon]] in the regular season in [[2018–19 Basketball Champions League|2018–19]]. This is the overall record for all Basketball Champions League matches. **[[Reyer Venezia Mestre|Reyer Venezia]] beat 108–101 (209 points) [[Banvit B.K.|Banvit]] in the regular season in [[2017–18 Basketball Champions League|2017–18]]. **[[Nanterre 92]] beat 102–106 (208 points) [[S.S. Felice Scandone|Felice Scandone]] in the regular season in [[2017–18 Basketball Champions League|2017–18]]. **[[s.S. Felice Scandone|Felice Scandone]] beat 105–102 (207 points) [[KK Włocławek|Włocławek]] in the regular season in [[2018–19 Basketball Champions League|2018–19]]. **[[AEK B.C.|AEK]] beat 101–103 (204 points) [[Reyer Venezia Mestre|Reyer Venezia]] in the regular season in [[2017–18 Basketball Champions League|2017–18]]. **[[Basketball Nymburk|Nymburk]] beat [[Telekom Baskets Bonn|Bonn]] by 106–98 (204 points) in the regular season in [[2017–18 Basketball Champions League|2017–18]]. This is the overall record of a match without overtimes in all Basketball Champions League matches. *[[AEK B.C.|AEK]] beat 94–100 (194 points) [[AS Monaco Basket|Monaco Basket]] in the final in [[2017–18 Basketball Champions League|2017–18]]. This is the overall record for the Basketball Champions League playoffs *[[Antwerp Giants]] beat 100–94 (194 points) [[Pallacanestro Cantù|Cantù]] in the qualifying round in [[2018–19 Basketball Champions League|2018–19]]. This is the overall record for the Basketball Champions League qualifying rounds
