===Specific regular season records=== ====14 wins==== No team won all the 14 matches of the regular season. [[AS Monaco Basket|Monaco]] won 13 in [[2017–18 Basketball Champions League|2017–18]]
====14 losses==== No team ended the regular season without wins. However, the worst performance was made by [[Bakken Bears]], by winning only one match and losing the other 13 games in [[2016–17 Basketball Champions League|2016–17]]
====Biggest disparity between group winner and runner-up==== The biggest wins difference between the first- and second-placed teams in a Champions League regular season is three wins, achieved by two teams: *[[Beşiktaş J.K. (men's basketball)|Beşiktaş]], 12 wins (+128) in [[2016–17 Basketball Champions League|2016–17]]. (2nd [[AEK Athens B.C.|AEK Athens]] 9 wins). *[[AS Monaco Basket|Monaco]], 13 wins (+239) in [[2017–18 Basketball Champions League|2017–18]]. (2nd [[Karşıyaka Basket|Karşıyaka]] 10 wins).
