{{infobox museum |name=Broel Museum |image=Broelmuseum.jpg |established=1981 |location=6 Broelkaai 8500, [[Kortrijk]], [[Belgium]] |visitors= |director= Isabelle De Jaegere |website={{official website|http://www.kortrijk.be/broelmuseum}} }}
The '''Broel Museum''' (Broelmuseum) was an [[art museum]], focusing on classical and applied arts of the 18th - 19th century. It's located on the [[Buda (Kortrijk)|Buda Island]] in [[Courtray]], [[Belgium]]. The building is a converted 18th-century [[Neoclassical architecture|neoclassical]] mansion, located at 6 Broelkaai. Since the end of 2014, the museum has closed its doors. Under the name of 'Broelkaai 6', the location is being turned into a platform for visual arts, and is scheduled to reopen in 2018.
==Exhibits== The main focus of the museum is artists from the area, or who are currently living in Kortijk, including; [[Roelant Savery]], [[Karel van Mander]], [[Kerstiaen De Keuninck]], [[Louis Pierre Verwee]], [[Évariste Carpentier]], [[Louis Robbe]], [[Edward Woutermaertens]], [[Joos Vincent de Vos]] with a prominence of art from the 16th and 19th centuries.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kortrijk.be/broelmuseum |title=Broelmuseum &#124; Stad Kortrijk |publisher=Kortrijk.be |date= |accessdate=2011-03-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110120144813/http://www.kortrijk.be/broelmuseum |archivedate=2011-01-20 |df= }}</ref>
