{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}}
{{Use British English|date=August 2015}}
'''''Painting the Century: 101 Portrait Masterpieces 1900–2000''''' was an international exhibition held at the [[National Portrait Gallery (London)|National Portrait Gallery]] in London in 2000–2001 that exhibited a painting representing each year of the [[20th-century art|20th century]]. A book of the same name was published by the National Portrait Gallery by [[Robin Warwick Gibson|Robin Gibson]] with an introduction by Professor [[Norbert Lynton]] that illustrates all works exhibited.

== Artists and subjects ==
Artists included [[Frank Auerbach]], [[Francis Bacon (painter)|Francis Bacon]], [[Salvador Dalí]], [[Otto Dix]], [[Lucian Freud]], [[Alberto Giacometti]], [[George Grosz]], [[Philip Harris (artist)|Philip Harris]], [[David Hockney]], [[Howard Hodgkin]], [[R. B. Kitaj]], [[Oskar Kokoschka]], [[Amedeo Modigliani]], [[Pablo Picasso]], [[John Singer Sargent]], [[Egon Schiele]],  [[Walter Sickert]], [[Marty St. James]].

The subjects included [[Anna Akhmatova]] by [[Kuzma Petrov-Vodkin]], [[Charlie Chaplin]] by [[Fernand Léger]], [[Edith Sitwell]] by [[Pavel Tchelitchew]], [[Leigh Bowery]] by [[Lucian Freud]], [[David Bowie]] and [[Iman (model)|Iman]] by [[Stephen Finer]], [[Vladimir Lenin]] by [[Isaak Brodsky]], a self-portrait by [[Edvard Munch]], [[Somerset Maugham]] by [[Graham Sutherland]], [[Elvis Presley]] by [[Andy Warhol]], [[Andy Warhol]] by [[Jean-Michel Basquiat]], ''Boy/Girl – the artists children'' by [[Marty St. James]].

== External links ==
* [http://www.npg.org.uk/live/prelcent.asp National Portrait Gallery exhibition description]
* [http://www.npg.org.uk/business/publications/painting-the-century.php  Details of the book of ''Painting the Century 101 Portrait Masterpieces 1900–2000'']    {{ISBN|1-85514-289-9}} (hardback); {{ISBN|1-85514-313-5}} (paperback)

