{{Notability|books|date=February 2018}}{{italic title}}
[[File:How It Works books.jpg|thumb|The 1995, 1996, Fall and Spring 1997, and Spring 1997 volumes of the How It Works science supplement.]]
'''''The Illustrated Science and Invention Encyclopedia''''' was an [[encyclopedia]] of books originally published in parts in the [[United Kingdom]] under the title ''How It Works'', by [[Marshall Cavendish|Marshall Cavendish Limited]],<ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/search?q=Illustrated+Science+and+Invention+Encyclopedia&fq=&dblist=638&start=21&qt=next_page]</ref> and republished in the United States in 1974 by H.S. Stuttman Publishers in [[Westport, Connecticut]], in 21 volumes (OCLC 3643238). It was supplanted by their ''The New Illustrated Science and Invention Encyclopedia: How It Works'', a 28 volume set edited by Donald Clarke and Mark Dartford, published in 1987 ({{ISBN|9780874754506}}) (OCLC 1333004714), and then republished in 28 volumes from 1989 to 1993 ({{ISBN|9780874754506}}),(OCLC 28822057). A 2003 edition numbered 20 volumes, and was well reviewed.<ref>{{cite web|title=How It Works|url=http://www.marshallcavendish.us/marshallcavendish-us/reference/catalog/science/comprehensive_science/0761473149.xml|accessdate=14 June 2017|deadurl=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120406104044/http://www.marshallcavendish.us/marshallcavendish-us/reference/catalog/science/comprehensive_science/0761473149.xml|archivedate=6 April 2012|df=}}</ref>

The encyclopedia was also published under the title "Science Horizons Year Books"<ref>Introduction. How It Works Science Supplement 1995. Ed. Lawrence T. Lorimer. N.p.: Grolier Incorporated, 1994. N. pag. Print. How It Works.</ref> and in a one-volume edition.{{Citation Needed|date=June 2017}}

